[1] Mozambique: update
Date: Tue 15 Jul 2014
Source: StarAfrica, APA (Agence Africaine de Presse) report [edited]
http://en.starafrica.com/news/mozambique-moves-to-fight-banana-disease.html


Mozambique moves to fight banana disease
----------------------------------------
Mozambique says plans are under way to roll out an ambitious 3 year plan to contain a deadly pathogenic form of the fusarium banana wilt. The project is expected to cost USD 370 000, with support of the UN Food and Agriculture Organization (FAO).

Recently, a destructive strain of the Panama disease [TR4; see ProMED-mail post 20131206.2095450] was discovered on a farm in the remote, agriculture-rich district of Monapo in the northern province of Nampula, after it devastated banana plantations in Asia over the past 2 decades. The Ministry of Agriculture says the authorities want to prevent it from spreading to new areas.

